sections.title: You now have access to the collection of WileyPLUS Digital Resources

activities.desc:
Dear Learners,


Welcome to a new learning experience through WileyPLUS Digital Resources.


Make available for you are the relevant learning resources such as adaptive practice, skills test, infographics, purposive reading materials, multimedia and animations that are embedded across 150 Digital Contents and 25 Subject Areas.

To navigate, feel free to explore any Title that is populated in each Subject Category in this Course through the following steps:

1. Open any section or Subject Category, e.g. Math and Statistics, either from Section Links on the right or from the categories below

2. Click a Title Link eg: Anton, Late Transcendentals, 11th Ed. You will be then directed to the WileyPLUS website

 3. Click Wiley Course Resources.

4. You will then have access to the following:

              1. E-Textbook

              2. Course Resources per Chapter

              3. Practice or Adaptive Learning Activities (may not be available in other Titles)
